This paper deals with securing tag-based recommender systems against attacks, which involves techniques related to information retrieval (IR) and security (CR). The use of machine learning algorithms such as Naive Bayes and Support Vector Machine suggests a focus on machine learning (LG) as well. Additionally, the use of synthetic data generated from del.icio.us dataset suggests a focus on databases (DB).
